Olam to Invest $35 Million in Mozambique Rice Production, O Pais Reports

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-07-28T02:17:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/olam-to-invest-35-million-in-mozambique-rice-production-o-pais-reports.html
Olam International Ltd. (OLAM) ’s
Mozambique unit will invest $35 million in rice production in
the central Zambezia province, independent daily O Pais
reported, citing a company official it didn’t identify.  Olam will provide the funds for between five and 10 years
to boost a system in the Tewe irrigation scheme that may lead to
production of 100,000 tons of rice a year, the Maputo based
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tim Smith at 
 tsmith58@bloomberg.net  